# MuseDAM Figma Component Mapper & Naming

## Trigger Conditions

- Figma link provided + any component/layer name mentioned
- Reskin or new component generation

## Step 1 — Extract & Name (from Figma layers)

Naming priority:

- Component/Instance → use ComponentNode.name (with variant: Button/Primary/Medium)
- Frame/Section → use as page/block name (e.g. IPLibraryPage, HeaderSection)
- Group/Auto Layout → semantic name or parent+child combination
- Atomic layers → only for internal className/data-testid

Naming convention:

- PascalCase: AssetCard, ConfirmDialog
- Variants with `/`: Button/Primary/Large
- If layers are generic (Frame 1, Group 45), warn user to rename in Figma

In code:

- File/export name = extracted semantic name
- MUST add `data-component="original Figma name"` to every major element

## Step 2 — Map to Local Components (priority order)

Check against existing project before creating anything new:

- Exact match in `src/components/ui/` (Button, Input, Card, Dialog, Table, etc.)
- Exact match in root business components (AssetThumbnail, ConfirmDialog, UserAvatar, UserSelect, etc.)
- Domain folders (approval-center/, dnd/, upload/, etc.)
- If an existing component already covers most of the target block, extend it with props or variants instead of creating a sibling component.

Mapping rules:

| Figma Layer | Local Component |
| --- | --- |
| Button/Primary/Medium | `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'` |
| Asset Card / IP Card | reuse `AssetThumbnail` or create in domain folder |
| Table | reuse or map to shadcn Table + MuseDAM styles |
| Icon node (SVG/vector) | `<Icon name="XXX" size={16} />` — check `public/icons/` first |
| Tabs | `import { Tabs, TabsList, TabsTrigger, TabsContent } from '@/components/ui/tabs'` |
| Badge/Tag | `import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'` |
| Avatar/UserAvatar | reuse `UserAvatar` from `@/components/UserAvatar` |
| Unknown | create in correct domain folder + add data-component comment |

If a shadcn component is referenced but `src/components/ui/[name].tsx` is missing, output the install command before writing code:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

Before code output, include:

- `Reuse manifest`
- `New components`
- `Why existing components were insufficient`
